      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my bathroom sink is doing that constant annoying drip even when i turn the handle all the way off. i think it's one of those older compression ones. what kind of tools do i need to fix it and what's the basic process to swap out the washer?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To replace the washer in your compression faucet, you'll need a flathead screwdriver, basin wrench, replacement washers, pliers, and some WD-40. Start by turning off the water supply. Apply WD-40 to loosen the faucet body, then use the basin wrench to remove the hex nuts holding the valve set in place. Take out the old washer and replace it with a new one. Reassemble the faucet, tighten the nuts back to their original tightness, and restore the water supply. Check for leaks and if they persist, repeat the process.",
