    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Carefully cleaning the buildup is a proactive step to ensure that all parts fit correctly and there's no compromise in the seal's integrity. Here's a simple cleaning procedure you can follow:\n\n1. Use a toothbrush and warm water to scrub the surface gently around the base area of the faucet handle. This will help remove any grime, soap scum, or buildup. Pat dry with a paper towel or let it dry naturally.\n\n2. For tougher residue, you can use a mild acidic cleaner (like vinegar) to help break down the gunk. Apply it to the area, let it sit for a few minutes, and then scrub again. Rinse the area thoroughly with water after cleaning.\n\n3. Inspect the rubber gasket and washer area. Look for any discoloration or deterioration that may indicate wear, which could affect a proper seal. Replace these components if necessary.\n\n4. Thoroughly dry and lubricate the decorative top of the faucet once it's clean and you're ready to replace the washer. This helps ensure a tight seal and prevents potential leaks due to dirt and debris.\n\nDon’t hesitate to double-check each step before proceeding, and if at any point you feel unsure, seeking professional assistance is always a safe choice.",
